	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: .ASM into .NES assistance</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Most assemblers have an <strong>INCBIN</strong> command you can use to <strong>INC</strong>lude <strong>BIN</strong>ary files. At the correct location in your ASM file (usually the very end) you can write this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;.incbin &quot;graphics.chr&quot;</div><br />This won't magically make tiles appear on the screen when you run the ROM though, you have to write a program that will put these tiles in the background.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


