	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><strong>DIS</strong>ASM6 is a <strong>dis</strong>assembler, it's meant to convert binary programs into ASM code, the exact opposite of what you want.<br /><br />Also, you are blindly writing stuff in the command prompt! The &quot;.incbin&quot; line is supposed to be written inside an ASM file, which then needs to be compiled. But like I said before, just including it won't do anything unless you write the code to use those tiles.<br /><br />I'll be honest with you: You are really, really, REALLY lost, you have absolutely no idea what you're doing. Nothing you're trying makes ANY sense. Programming isn't something you guess. You can't just download a bunch of programs and type random stuff hoping it will work. You have to study!<br /><br />We have suggested several times that you follow <a href="http://www.nintendoage.com/pub/faq/NA/nerdy_nights_out.html" class="postlink">this tutorial</a>. Please stop guessing and read this. Believe me, NES programming isn't like Photoshop, which you can poke around and learn by yourself, you won't learn NES programming like this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


